{"name": "krecviz", "metadata": {"name": "krecviz", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/kscalelabs/krecviz", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["krec", "numpy", "scipy", "scipy-stubs", "Pillow", "types-Pillow", "rerun-sdk", "tqdm", "types-tqdm", "trimesh", "urdf_parser_py"], "summary": "Visualisation utilities for krec files", "upload_time": 1734758212}, "documentation": ["# krecviz\nVisualisation utilities for krec files \n\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9d53e560-f6d4-42d0-a5df-b6ef6aa26ab2)\n\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install git+https://github.com/kscalelabs/krecviz.git\n# or clone the repo and run\npip install -e .\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nNOTE: For now, in the rerun viwer, make sure to select \"log tick\" as the time unit. will fx this soon\n\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/360e1e22-3dbf-4382-b21e-da85174f9206)\n\n\nCLI usage:\n\n```bash\n# cd to the repo root\ncd krecviz\npython visualize.py --urdf data/urdf_examples/gpr/robot.urdf --krec data/krec_examples/actuator_22_right_arm_shoulder_roll_movement.krec --output output.rrd\n```\n\nPython API usage:\n\n```python\nimport krecviz\n\nkrecviz.viz(\n    krec_path=\"path/to/recording.krec\",\n    urdf_path=\"path/to/robot.urdf\"\n)\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "krecviz", "documentation": ["Visualization utilities for KREC files."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "krecviz.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "krecviz.viz", "xref": {"fqname": "krecviz.visualize.visualize_krec", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "krecviz.visualize", "documentation": ["Visualize KREC recordings with URDF models using Rerun.\n\nThis script loads a KREC recording and animates it on a URDF model, displaying\njoint positions, velocities, and torques over time.\n\nNOTE: You cannot both save the visualization to a file and log to an open Rerun viewer.\n\nUsage:\n    # Basic usage with default paths\n    python visualize.py\n\n    # Specify custom URDF and KREC files\n    python visualize.py --urdf path/to/robot.urdf --krec path/to/recording.krec\n\n    # Save the visualization to a Rerun file\n    python visualize.py --output my_animation.rrd"], "functions": [{"name": "krecviz.visualize.load_krec", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "verbose", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "krec.KRec", "xref": {"fqname": "krec.KRec", "project": "krec"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Smart loader that handles both direct KREC and MKV-embedded KREC files."]}, {"name": "krecviz.visualize.update_robot_pose", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "entity_to_transform", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}]}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "actuator_states", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "krec.ActuatorState", "xref": {"fqname": "krec.ActuatorState", "project": "krec"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "joint_name_to_enti